#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:2
msgid "CQRS"
msgstr "CQRS"

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:4
msgid ""
"The flow of the simplest `CRUD "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Create,_read,_update_and_delete>`__ "
"applications can be described using the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:8
msgid ""
"Controllers layer handle **HTTP requests** and delegate tasks to the "
"services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:10
msgid ""
"Services layer is a place where the most of the business logic is being "
"done."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:12
msgid "**Services** uses Repositories / DAOs to change / persist entities."
msgstr "**Services** uses Repositories / DAOs to change / persist entities."

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:13
msgid "Entities act as containers for the values, with setters and getters."
msgstr "Entities act as containers for the values, with setters and getters."

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:15
msgid ""
"In most cases, there are no reasons to make small and medium-sized "
"applications more complex. However, sometimes it’s not enough and when "
"our needs become **more sophisticated** we want to have scalable systems "
"with straightforward data flow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:20
msgid ""
"Hence, we provide a lightweight `CQRS module "
"<https://github.com/nestjs/cqrs>`__ which elements are described below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:25
msgid "Commands"
msgstr "Commands"

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:27
msgid ""
"In order to make the application easier to understand, each change has to"
" be preceded by **Command**. When any command is dispatched, the "
"application has to react on it. Commands can be dispatched from the "
"services (or directly from the controllers/gateways) and consumed in "
"corresponding **Command Handlers**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:61
msgid ""
"Here’s a sample service that dispatches ``KillDragonCommand``. Let’s see "
"how the command looks like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:81
msgid ""
"The ``CommandBus`` is a commands **stream**. It delegates commands to the"
" equivalent handlers. Each command has to have corresponding **Command "
"Handler**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:117
msgid ""
"Now every application state change is a result of the **Command** "
"occurrence. The logic is encapsulated in handlers. If we want, we can "
"simply add logging here or even more, we can persist our commands in the "
"database (e.g. for the diagnostics purposes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:123
msgid "Events"
msgstr "Events"

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:125
msgid ""
"Since we have encapsulated commands in handlers, we prevent interaction "
"between them - the application structure is still not flexible, not "
"**reactive**. The solution is to use **events**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:146
msgid ""
"Events are asynchronous. They are dispatched either by **models** or "
"directly using ``EventBus``. In order to dispatch events, models have to "
"extend the ``AggregateRoot`` class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:176
msgid ""
"The ``apply()`` method does not dispatch events yet because there’s no "
"relationship between model and the ``EventPublisher`` class. How to "
"associate the model and the publisher? We need to use a publisher "
"``mergeObjectContext()`` method inside our command handler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:219
msgid ""
"Now everything works as expected. Notice that we need to ``commit()`` "
"events since they’re not being dispatched immediately. Obviosuly, an "
"object doesn’t have to exist upfront. We can easily merge type context as"
" well:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:229
msgid ""
"That’s it. A model has an ability to publish events now. And we have to "
"handle them. Additionally, we could emit events manually using "
"``EventBus``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:239
msgid "info **Hint** The ``EventBus`` is an injectable class."
msgstr "info **Hint** The ``EventBus`` is an injectable class."

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:241
msgid "Each event can have multiple **Event Handlers**."
msgstr "Each event can have multiple **Event Handlers**."

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:255
msgid "Now we can move the **write logic** into the event handlers."
msgstr "Now we can move the **write logic** into the event handlers."

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:258
msgid "Sagas"
msgstr "Sagas"

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:260
msgid ""
"This type of **Event-Driven Architecture** improves application "
"**reactiveness and scalability**. Now, when we have events, we can simply"
" react to them in various ways. The **Sagas** are the last building block"
" from the architecture point of view."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:265
msgid ""
"The sagas are an incredibly powerful feature. Single saga may listen for "
"1..\\* events. It can combine, merge, filter […] events streams. `RxJS "
"<https://github.com/ReactiveX/rxjs>`__ library is the place where the "
"magic comes from. In simple words, each saga has to return an Observable "
"which contains a command. This command is dispatched **asynchronously**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:299
msgid ""
"info **Hint** The ``ofType`` operator is exported from the "
"``@nestjs/cqrs`` package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:302
msgid ""
"We declared a rule - when any hero kills the dragon, the ancient item is "
"being dropped. Afterwards, the ``DropAncientItemCommand`` will be "
"dispatched and processed by the appropriate handler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:307
msgid "Queries"
msgstr "Queries"

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:309
msgid ""
"The ``CqrsModule`` might be also handy for queries processing. The "
"``QueryBus`` works the same as ``CommandsBus``. Also, query handlers "
"should implement the ``IQueryHandler`` interface and be marked with the "
"``@QueryHandler()`` decorator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:315 ../../source/recipes/documentation.rst:9
msgid "Setup"
msgstr "Setup"

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:317
msgid ""
"The last thing which we have to take care of is to set up the whole "
"mechanism."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:340
msgid "Summary"
msgstr "Summary"

#: ../../source/recipes/cqrs.rst:342
msgid ""
"``CommandBus``, ``QueryBus`` and ``EventBus`` are **Observables**. It "
"means that you can easily subscribe to the whole stream and enrich your "
"application with **Event Sourcing**."
msgstr ""

