#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:2
msgid "Health checks (Terminus)"
msgstr "Health checks (Terminus)"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:4
msgid ""
"The `terminus <https://github.com/godaddy/terminus>`__ offers hooks to "
"react on graceful shutdowns and supports you creating proper `Kubernetes "
"<https://kubernetes.io/>`__ readiness / liveness checks for any HTTP "
"application. The module "
"[@nestjs/terminus](https://github.com/nestjs/terminus) integrates the "
"terminus library with the Nest ecosystem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:14
msgid ""
"To get started with ``@nestjs/terminus`` we need to install the required "
"dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:22
msgid "Setting up a health check"
msgstr "Setting up a health check"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:24
msgid ""
"A health check represents a summary of **health indicators**. A health "
"indicator executes a check of a service, whether it is in a healthy state"
" or not. A health check is positive, if all the assigned health "
"indicators are up and running. Because a lot of applications will need "
"similar health indicators, "
"[@nestjs/terminus](https://github.com/nestjs/terminus) provides a set of "
"predefined health indicators, such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:32
msgid "``DNSHealthIndicator``"
msgstr "``DNSHealthIndicator``"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:33
msgid "``TypeOrmHealthIndicator``"
msgstr "``TypeOrmHealthIndicator``"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:34
msgid "``MongooseHealthIndicator``"
msgstr "``MongooseHealthIndicator``"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:35
msgid "``MicroserviceHealthIndicator``"
msgstr "``MicroserviceHealthIndicator``"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:36
msgid "``MemoryHealthIndicator``"
msgstr "``MemoryHealthIndicator``"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:37
msgid "``DiskHealthIndicator``"
msgstr "``DiskHealthIndicator``"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:40
msgid "DNS Health Check"
msgstr "DNS Health Check"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:42
msgid ""
"The first step to get started with our first health check, is to setup a "
"service which will associate health indicators to an endpoint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:98
msgid ""
"Once we have set up our ``TerminusOptionsService``, we can import the "
"``TerminusModule`` into the root ``ApplicationModule``. The "
"``TerminusOptionsService`` will provide the settings, which in turn will "
"be used by the ``TerminusModule``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:121
msgid ""
"info **Hint** If done correctly, Nest will expose the defined health "
"check(s), which are reachable through a GET request to the defined route."
" For example ``curl -X GET 'http://localhost:3000/health'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:126
msgid "Custom health indicator"
msgstr "Custom health indicator"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:128
msgid ""
"In some cases, the predefined health indicators provided by "
"``@nestjs/terminus`` do not cover all of your health check requirements. "
"In this case you can set up a custom health indicator according to your "
"needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:133
msgid ""
"Let’s get started by creating a service which will represent our custom "
"health indicator. To get a basic understanding how a health indicator is "
"structured, we will create an example ``DogHealthIndicator``. This health"
" indicator should have the state “up”, if every ``Dog`` object has the "
"type ``goodboy``, otherwise it will throw an error, which then the health"
" indicator will be seen as “down”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:193
msgid ""
"The next thing we need to do is registering the health indicator as a "
"provider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:218
msgid ""
"info **Hint** In a real world application the ``DogHealthIndicator`` "
"should be provided in a separate module, for example ``DogsModule``, "
"which then will be imported by the ``ApplicationModule``. But keep in "
"mind to add the ``DogHealthIndicator`` to the ``exports`` array of the "
"``DogModule`` and add the ``DogModule`` in ``imports`` array of the "
"``TerminusModule.forRootAsync()`` parameter object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:225
msgid ""
"The last required thing to do is to add the now available health "
"indicator in the required health check endpoint. For that we go back to "
"our ``TerminusOptionsService`` and implement it to the ``/health`` "
"endpoint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:283
msgid ""
"If everything has been done correctly, the ``/health`` endpoint should "
"respond with a ``503`` response code and the following data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:298
msgid ""
"You can view working examples in the ``@nestjs/terminus`` `repository "
"<https://github.com/nestjs/terminus/tree/master/sample>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:302
msgid "Custom Logger"
msgstr "Custom Logger"

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:304
msgid ""
"The ``Terminus`` module automatically logs every error during a health "
"check request. By default, it will use the globally defined Nest logger. "
"You can read more about the global logger in the `Logger chapter "
"<https://docs.nestjs.com/techniques/logger>`__. In some cases, you want "
"to handle the logs of ``Terminus`` explicitly. In this case, the "
"``TerminusModule.forRoot[Async]`` function offers an option for a custom "
"logger."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/recipes/terminus.rst:322
msgid "The logger can also be disabled by setting the logger option to ``null``."
msgstr "The logger can also be disabled by setting the logger option to ``null``."

